law.text:
It shall be unlawful for any owner or operator of any transfer station to:
Operate a transfer station without having a transfer station license;
Fail to comply with administrative regulations promulgated by the director for the proper storage, handling, and transport of producers' milk samples while at the transfer station and en route to the testing laboratory;
Manipulate, substitute, or falsify any producer milk weights or milk samples;
Transfer milk, samples, or records at a transfer station without having a current sampler-weigher's license;
Transfer milk that has not been sampled and weighed at the farm by a licensed sampler-weigher;
Fail to notify the director in writing of any knowledge of an inaccurately calibrated bulk milk tank; or
Hinder or obstruct any authorized person in the performance of his or her duties under KRS 260.775 to 260.845.
